The tool he used, a mini hockey stick wrapped in insulator to prevent an electric shock to the solar panels, which generate several hundred volts, had been devised and "crafted" by the astronauts aboard the station.
When the action was over, Scott Parazynski waited for the manifold to be fully folded before counting his tools and returning to the station.
